Introduction
With the group split due to internal confliction. We have created our own program with 10 different rules within the short time period. The design and 

RULES
READ USER INPUT
APPLY RULES (if a rule is broken the class returns a true value otherwise it returns a false)
1) Check first character of sentence if its not capitalized return a true value for rule 1
2) Check last word of sentence and if it doesn’t have either a question mark, exclamation mark, or a period return a true value for rule 2
3) Check each word of the sentence and make sure the character between them is a single space character, if it isn’t return a true value for rule 3
4) Check each word individually and if it has a symbol anywhere from the start to before the last character return a true value for rule 4
5) Check the sentence for nouns and verbs, if there aren't any return a true value for rule 5
6) Check each word individually and if it has a number(s) from between in front of the first character to the end of the word return a true value for rule 6
7) Check the sentence for the word are and if it's there make sure the word before is a noun and it is a plural, if not return a true value for rule 7
8) Check the sentence for an apostrophe character and if there is one, check the word it's in against a list of contracted words and if it doesn’t match any return a true value for rule 8
9) Check each word for any letter character repeated three times back to back and if there is return a true value for rule 9
10) Check each word against a dictionary of correctly spelled words to make sure each word is spelled correctly if any word is misspelled return a true value for rule 10

Grammar Checker

1) Output string saying you didn’t capitalize first character of the sentence
2) Output string saying you didn’t end the sentence with proper punctuation
3) Output string saying you either double spaced or put a symbol character instead of a space between words
4) Output string saying you put a symbol inside of a word and if possible show the word where error occurred
5) Output string saying you forgot either a noun or verb, depending on if it was both or just one
6) Output string saying you misplaced a number and if possible where
7) Output string saying you didn't properly pluralize something and if possible what word
8) Output string saying you didn't use a contraction correctly and if possible what word
9) Output string saying you used too many of a single character in a row
10) Output string saying you misspelled single or multiple words and identify the word
